    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Help user to split WordPress post/page into multiple pages easier using WPEditor button.<br />\nSee more description here</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thinhknowscode.com/how-to-separate-wordpress-single-post-into-multiple-pages/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">How to split WordPress post into multiple pages</a></p>\n<p>If the navigation section does not appear, this is probably because your theme is unable to handle the tag for splitting the page. So you need to add the following code in your single.php loop:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;?php wp_link_pages(); ?&gt;\n</code></pre>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the entire &#8216;tkc-sliced-post&#8217; directory to the &#8216;/wp-content/plugins/&#8217; directory.</li>\n<li>Activate TKC Sliced Post through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Help user to split Wordpress post/page into multiple pages easier using WPEditor button.",
    "description": "<p>Help user to split WordPress post/page into multiple pages easier using WPEditor button.<br />\nSee more description here</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thinhknowscode.com/how-to-separate-wordpress-single-post-into-multiple-pages/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">How to split WordPress post into multiple pages</a></p>\n<p>If the navigation section does not appear, this is probably because your theme is unable to handle the tag for splitting the page. So you need to add the following code in your single.php loop:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;?php wp_link_pages(); ?&gt;\n</code></pre>\n",
